@page "/blog/debt-free-plan"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@inherits BlogPostBase

<PageTitle>SmartBudget - How to Get Out of Debt</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/blog.css" />

<div class="blog-post-page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-door"></i> Home</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/blog">Blog</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">Debt-Free Plan</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
        </div>

        <article class="blog-post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <span class="post-category-badge">Debt Management</span>
                <h1>How to Get Out of Debt: A Step-by-Step Plan</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span><i class="bi bi-person-circle"></i> Chidi Okonkwo</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-calendar3"></i> @CurrentDate</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-clock"></i> 7 min read</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="post-body-content">
                <p>Getting out of debt is one of the most important steps to financial freedom. This step-by-step plan will help you become debt-free in @CurrentYear.</p>

                <h2>Step 1: List All Your Debts</h2>
                <p>Write down every debt you have:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Credit card balances</li>
                    <li>Personal loans</li>
                    <li>Student loans</li>
                    <li>Car loans</li>
                    <li>Mortgage</li>
                    <li>Money owed to family and friends</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 2: Know Your Numbers</h2>
                <p>For each debt, note:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Total balance</li>
                    <li>Interest rate</li>
                    <li>Minimum monthly payment</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 3: Choose a Debt Repayment Strategy</h2>
                <h3>Method 1: Debt Avalanche</h3>
                <p>Pay off debts with the highest interest rates first. This saves you the most money in interest.</p>

                <h3>Method 2: Debt Snowball</h3>
                <p>Pay off the smallest debt first, then move to the next. This gives you quick wins and motivation.</p>

                <h2>Step 4: Create a Budget</h2>
                <p>Allocate as much money as possible to debt repayment. Cut unnecessary expenses.</p>

                <h2>Step 5: Increase Your Income</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Get a side hustle</li>
                    <li>Ask for a raise</li>
                    <li>Freelance in your skill area</li>
                    <li>Sell items you don't need</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 6: Negotiate with Creditors</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ask for lower interest rates</li>
                    <li>Request payment plans</li>
                    <li>Consider debt consolidation</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 7: Stay Motivated</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Track your progress</li>
                    <li>Celebrate milestones</li>
                    <li>Visualize a debt-free future</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Take Control of Your Debt</h3>
                    <p>Track your debt repayment progress with SmartBudget.</p>
                    <a href="/Account/Register" class="btn-cta">Get Started Free →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>



@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        PageName = "blog-post";
        await base.OnInitializedAsync();
    }
}